{"questionId":"9076583","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A capacitor consists of two parallel square plates separated by a vacuum. The plates are 2.5 cm × 2.5 cm squares. The capacitance of the capacitor is 4.3 pF.&nbsp;</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>In a different circuit, a transformer is connected to an alternating current (ac) supply.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4806/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-13_om_14.19.37.png\" alt=\"M18/4/PHYSI/HP2/ENG/TZ1/07.d\"></p>\n<p>The transformer has 100 turns in the primary coil and 1200 turns in the secondary coil. The peak value of the voltage of the ac supply is 220 V. Determine the root mean square (rms) value of the output voltage.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 1</em></strong></p>\n<p><em>ε<sub>s</sub></em> = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{1200}}{{100}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>1200</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;× 220</p>\n<p>= 2640&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>V<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>V<sub>rms</sub> = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{2640}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2640</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span> =&nbsp;1870&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>V<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong><em>ALTERNATIVE 2</em></strong></p>\n<p>(Primary) V<sub>rms</sub> = <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{220}}{{\\sqrt 2 }}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>220</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <msqrt>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </msqrt>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;= 156&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>V<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>(Secondary) V<sub>rms</sub>&nbsp;= <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{156 \\times 1200}}{{100}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>156</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>1200</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>V<sub>rms</sub> = 1870&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>V<strong>»</strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Allow ECF from MP1 and MP2.</em></p>\n<p><em>Award </em><strong><em>[2] </em></strong><em>max for 12.96 V (reversing N</em><sub><em>p </em></sub><em>and N</em><sub><em>s</em></sub><em>).</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[3 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9076583","referenceCode":"18M.2.HL.TZ1.7d","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"In a different circuit, a transformer is connected to an alternating current (ac) supply. The transformer has 100 turns in the primary coil and 1200 turns in the secondary coil. Th","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction","11.2 – Power generation and transmission","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 11: Electromagnetic induction"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}